Context:
Program Information:
- The program offers advanced technical abilities with a focus on communication, teamwork, and client service skills.
- Students will learn about project-based and experiential learning, AI and machine-learning strategies and development, mobile application development, full-stack development, software development life cycle and methodologies, and database management.
- Changes to the program may occur and are made in consultation with the Program Advisory Committee.
- Required computer specifications: 16 GB RAM minimum, 256 GB SSD Hard Drive (500+ GB is optimal), Quad-core i7 2.4GHz or better, Video card (2GB RAM minimum/4GB RAM recommended), and a webcam.
- Career opportunities include database administration, systems analysis and design, consulting, application design and development, web application design and development, data architect (AI/ Machine Learning), full-stack developer, mobile application developer, and many others.
- Graduates may find systems development work for corporate clients and smaller contract companies as programmer analysts.
- Transfer credits are available towards further study to attain a degree.

Required Courses:
- Semester 1: COMP 1151 (IT Essentials), COMP 1236 (Fundamentals of Computing Logic), COMP 1234 (Introduction To Web Development), GSSC 1027 (Personal Finance), MATH 1162 (Mathematics for Computer Technology I), COMM 2000 (Communicating Across Contexts).
- Semester 2: COMP 1168 (Database Management), COMP 1202 (Object-Oriented Programming), COMP 1235 (Introduction To Full-Stack Development), COMP 3044 (Linux Essentials), MATH 1172 (Mathematics for Computer Technology II).

Note: Enrolling in January requires completion of semester 2 from May to August of the same year.

- Apply project management principles and tools when responding to requirements and monitoring projects within a computing environment.

Context:
The Computer Programmer Analyst program is offered through George Brown College's School of Computer Technology from the Casa Loma Campus located at 146 Kendal Avenue. Mature students who are 19 years or older and do not have an Ontario Secondary School Diploma (OSSD) may take the Admissions Assessment for English and Math, or consider upgrading to achieve the required credits in those subjects. Applicants should note that meeting the minimum requirements does not guarantee admission to the program, as applicants may be required to have higher grades than stated.

Domestic students should apply through Ontario Colleges. International students should apply through the George Brown College Online Application System and visit the International Admissions page for country-specific admission requirements. The School of Computer Technology can be contacted at 416-415-5000, ext. 4287 or computertechnology@georgebrown.ca during office hours Monday – Friday: 9 a.m. – 4 p.m. Maziar Masoudi, the Program Co-ordinator, can be reached at 416-415-5000, ext. 3345 or mmasoudi@georgebrown.ca for more information about the program.

Additional related programs offered by George Brown College include Computer Systems Technology (T147) and Computer Systems Technician (T141). The college may grant course exemptions based on previous college or university credits, and further information can be found on the Transfer Guide. International students are encouraged to contact one of George Brown's international recruitment representatives for personalized assistance. Campus tours and information sessions can be booked to learn more about George Brown College and its programs.
